{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014rtLZfs2nv4bmUai4PyFNE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The CockroachDB cluster is fully operational. Here's a summary of what was diagnosed and what happened:\n\n---\n\n## Diagnosis\n\nThe cluster was configured correctly (headless service with `publishNotReadyAddresses: true`, `--join` listing all 3 peers, `--advertise-addr` using pod DNS names). The initial logs showed two types of join errors:\n\n1. **\"connection refused\"** — all 3 pods started simultaneously (Parallel policy) before each other's CockroachDB processes were listening. Transient, expected.\n2. **\"no such host\"** — intermittent DNS propagation delay for the headless service entries at startup. Transient, resolved within seconds.\n\nNo configuration change was needed. The cluster self-organized:\n- `crdb-cluster-0` bootstrapped itself as node 1 after exhausting retries\n- `crdb-cluster-1` and `crdb-cluster-2` joined as nodes 3 and 2\n\n## Final State\n\n| Node | Pod | `is_available` | `is_live` |\n|------|-----|----------------|-----------|\n| 1 | crdb-cluster-0 | true | true |\n| 2 | crdb-cluster-2 | true | true |\n| 3 | crdb-cluster-1 | true | true |\n\n- **SQL accepts connections** via both pod DNS names and the `crdb-cluster-public` ClusterIP service\n- **All ranges fully replicated** (0 underreplicated ranges) — rebalancing completed ~5 minutes after join\n- **DDL/DML verified**: `CREATE DATABASE`, `CREATE TABLE`, `INSERT`, `SELECT` all succeed"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":581,"cache_read_input_tokens":48794,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":581},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c86dacff-e511-4cd8-a845-0f0cf90987cb","uuid":"f0